<rubble:addonmeta
	header=`Allows you to set a population cap that will override the default for this world.`
	
	description=`
This addon will take the values you enter (use the config var editor) and create a DFHack
script that will set the population caps as specified whenever the fortress is loaded.

This will cause DF to completely ignore the setting in the init files (for worlds that use this addon)!

The default values (as loaded from the init files) should be automatically restored when the world is unloaded.
`
	
	vars=<map
		population_cap=<rubble:addonmetavar name='DF Population Cap' val="200">
		strict_population_cap=<rubble:addonmetavar name='DF Strict Population Cap' val="220">
		baby_cap_absolute=<rubble:addonmetavar name='DF Child Cap (Absolute)' val="100">
		baby_cap_percent=<rubble:addonmetavar name='DF Child Cap (Percent)' val="1000">
	>
>